race.comment: ROHESIA (7) resumes. She's a promising filly who was running in some strong races last time in, beaten a head in a Listed race at Moonee Valley two back, fifth in a strong G3 behind Inkaruna and My Gladiola at Caulfield before a break. She looks very well placed here with natural improvement. ALERO (2) proved far too good winning well at Sandown Hillside second up over 1300m. He gets every chance up on speed from a good gate again and can make it a double. PICK 'N' MIX (5) made nice improvement second up here when going down narrowly to a handy one in Foxenberg. She's always promised a bit and looks to be heading the right way. BRUTALINA (8) can be an improver down in grade off some even runs in Sydney.
